  <subfield code="o">1</subfield>
  <subfield code="m">An incident ray intersects a cylinder, defining a point Ap</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="o">2</subfield>
  <subfield code="m">The ray is refracted twice at the boundary, giving the point Bp. The following set of equations describes these refraction steps: \begin{equation*} \begin{align*} \begin{eqnarray} \theta^1_{B_p}&amp;= -\theta^1_{A_p}, \end{eqnarray} \end{align*}</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="m">\tag{ 1 }</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="m">\end{equation*}</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="m">\begin{equation*} \begin{align*} \begin{eqnarray} \theta_{B_p}&amp;= \theta_{A_p}+2\arcsin\biggl(\frac{\sin(\theta^1_{A_p})}{n}\biggr), \end{eqnarray} \end{align*}</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="m">\tag{ 2 }</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="m">\end{equation*}</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="m">where n is the optical index of the cylinders</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="o">3</subfield>
  <subfield code="m">The ray propagates in air until it hits a new cylinder, this gives A_{p+1} and the process goes on. The couple (\theta_{A_{p+1}},\theta^1_{A_{p+1}}) is found with the help of the equations</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="m">\begin{equation*} \begin{align*} \begin{eqnarray} &amp;f_B(x)=\tan(\alpha)[x-R \cos(\theta_{B_p})]\nonumber\\ &amp;+R \sin(\theta_{B_p}), \end{eqnarray} \end{align*}</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="m">\tag{ 3 }</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="m">\end{equation*}</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="m">\begin{equation*} \begin{align*} \begin{eqnarray} &amp;(x_{A_{(p+1)}}-x^c_{p+1})^2 \nonumber\\ &amp;+(f_B(x_{A_{(p+1)}})-y^c_{p+1})^2=R^2, \end{eqnarray} \end{align*}</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="m">\tag{ 4 }</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="m">\end{equation*} where α is the angle between the horizontal axis and the ray as depicted in fig., 1: #epl18363fig1(b). It satisfies \alpha=\theta_{B_p}+\theta^1_{B_p}=\theta_{A_{(p+1)}}+\theta^1_{A_{(p+1)}}.(x^c_{p+1},y^c_{p+1}) are the cylinder coordinates at the (p + 1)-th collision</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
